Lord Adonis will announce whether or not he believes the project should be put in place, but longer public consultations and planning procedures mean that a final decision will not be made before a general election.
Even if it launches the machine, the network will have to be built part by part.
Trains will first be forced to travel off high-speed lines on existing tracks north of Birmingham, keeping travel times between London and Scotland longer than three hours.
This seems to be the best solution to ensure a transition from aircraft to trains, which is a reference point for the rail revolution.
