I hope that your country will soon be recognised by the United Nations, said Alexei Ostrovski, a member of the Russian parliament, by raising a glass of vodka.
For its part, the opposition represented in the ballot by former Vice-President Raoul Khadjimba and two businessmen, Zaous Ardzinba and Beslan Boutba, criticizes the agreements concluded with Moscow last year, such as the one giving control over the Abkhaz railways to Russia for 10 years.
The fifth candidate, Vitali Bganba, says he does not support the current power or the opposition.
A 50% majority plus one vote is required to win the election.
