New tools for car expertise
In these days of bad weather and accidents, car garages are not the only winners.
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered a disaster are brought back to a garage, where an expert must assess the damage and the cost of repair.
Each claim is different, and the calculation of the cost of parts and labour time can be a long and complex task.
Calculating by hand the cost of a repair between 20 000 and 30 000 euros, including coins and labour can take two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the help of the latest IT tools, it would be a matter of minutes.
For this reason, almost 100% of experts use such systems.
Providers of claims assessment and maintenance services and solutions are dedicated to collecting information provided by manufacturers, then processing it and offering it to their customers as a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, of the North American group Solera, is the leading company; 80% of the estimates are made with its products.
Other companies competing in the field of evaluation tools and the development of information on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
The work with the data provided by the manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, the company in Spain with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them provides them with information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed has been steadily increasing, with the result that over the last five years more versions, variants and engines have been launched than in the previous 15 years.
When a new car comes out on the market, these companies get to work.
This is a very difficult task, because it is necessary to catalogue each of the thousand parts of the vehicle and record its price.
In addition, a "smart" graphic image of each model is created on which you can click on the different parts of a passenger car.
If it is a massively sold model, the work can be ready in a week if the process progresses very quickly.
If it is a low-selling car, it may take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information on 99.2% of cars marketed in Spain.
